    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Removal -
        Glow Plug Sleeves
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s10.2.10" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Glow Plug Sleeves</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, if replacing glow plug sleeves in chassis, put a small plug in the
                    bottom of the glow plug sleeve before cutting threads. The plug will prevent small metal chips from
                    entering the combustion chamber.
                </para>
            </caution>
            <note>
                <para>Glow plug sleeve removal is not required unless sleeves are damaged.</para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>Use
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">Glow Plug Sleeve Remover ZTSE4531</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s10.t3"/>
                    to remove glow plug sleeves.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3450010040" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08142.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow Plug Sleeve Remover ZTSE4531</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Thread tap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow plug sleeve remover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The glow plug sleeve is made of stainless steel. Lubrication of the thread tap is required.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate thread tap.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010041" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08134.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow plug sleeve tap (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert thread tap into glow plug sleeve.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut at least 19 mm (0.75 in) deep threads to accommodate glow plug sleeve remover.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010042" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08136.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow Plug Sleeve Remover ZTSE4531 installed</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread Glow Plug Sleeve Remover ZTSE4531 into glow plug sleeve and tighten bolt until sleeve
                is extracted.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard glow plug sleeve.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
